%global __brp_check_rpaths %{nil}
%global packname  fractional
%global packver   0.1.3
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          0.1.3
Release:          3%{?dist}%{?buildtag}
Summary:          Vulgar Fractions in R

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildRequires:    R-CRAN-Rcpp 
Requires:         R-CRAN-Rcpp 

%description
The main function of this package allows numerical vector objects to be
displayed with their values in vulgar fractional form.  This is convenient
if patterns can then be more easily detected.  In some cases replacing the
components of a numeric vector by a rational approximation can also be
expected to remove some component of round-off error.  The main functions
form a re-implementation of the functions 'fractions' and 'rational' of
the MASS package, but using a radically improved programming strategy.

